            Brazil under tariff pressure
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image
          border-radius="10px"
          padding="10px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/us-sanctions-brazilian-judge-bolsonaro-investigation.jpg"
          alt="The US administration's ire has been directed at the Brazilian Supreme Court judge in charge of investigating Bolsonaro"
          href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com"
        />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>
              The US administration's ire has been directed at the Brazilian
              Supreme Court judge in charge of investigating Bolsonaro. Credits:
              Reuters</i
            >
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The what:</strong> President Trump imposed a 50% tariff on
            Brazil to address its policies harming US companies, foreign policy,
            and the economy. He accused Brazil of demanding content moderation
            and user data under threat of penalty. He also condemned the
            prosecution of former Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro and imposed
            sanctions on the Brazilian Supreme Court Judge (<a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-1-aug-25-spotlight-h1-1-fact-sheet?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >fact sheet</a
            >).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The why:</strong> Trump asserts that these tariffs are a
            retaliation for the
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-1-aug-25-spotlight-h1-2-prosecution-of-jair-bolsonaro?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >prosecution of Jair Bolsonaro</a
            >, his ally. Bolsonaro denies the assertions of a 2022 coup attempt
            but acknowledges attempting to reverse the election results. The US
            president also condemned the Brazilian Supreme Court judge’s orders
            to shut down Bolsonaro’s social media account for spreading
            disinformation.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The reaction:</strong> Brazil has
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-1-aug-25-spotlight-h1-3-criticized-the-sanctions?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >criticized the sanctions</a
            >
            on the judge and condemned the US for interfering in its justice
            system. The Brazilian Treasury Secretary said the political motives
            behind the tariffs undermine national sovereignty and the historical
            relationship between the two countries.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
