        <mj-image
          border-radius="10px"
          padding="10px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/global-connection-flags-map-us-nigeria-lithuania-pakistan-myanmar-korea.jpg"
          alt="Map showing international connections with flags of the United States, Nigeria, Lithuania, Pakistan, Myanmar, and South Korea marked across a global arc"
          href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com"
        />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p
            style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.5;
              padding-top: 0px;
              padding-bottom: 6px;
            "
          >
            <strong>🇲🇲 Myanmar- State of emergency ended.</strong> Myanmar’s
            junta has ended its four-year state of emergency ahead of elections
            planned for December 2025. The election is widely criticized by
            international bodies, boycotted by the opposition group, and seen as
            an attempt to legitimize military rule. A recent law punishes
            election-related dissent with up to 10 years of imprisonment (<a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-01-08-2025-burmese-political-tension?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >Burmese political tensions</a
            >).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
            <strong>🇰🇷 South Korea - Population stagnation.</strong> South
            Korea’s population had no growth in 2024. Reports showed that the
            total population reached 51.8Mn, an increase of 31,000 from the
            previous year, or 0.1%. The rise in foreign residents offset the
            decline in Korean nationals. Nearly one-fifth of the population is
            over 65 (<a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-1-aug-25-worldwide-9-demographics-shift?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >demographics shift</a
            >).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
            <strong> 🇵🇰 Pakistan - Oil agreement.</strong> President Trump
            announced an agreement with Pakistan to develop its oil reserves,
            while Pakistan said it would lower US tariffs on its exports.
            Pakistan hailed the arrangement as a "win-win," suggesting stronger
            trade and funding between the two nations. The move follows Trump's
            imposition of a 25% tariff on India (<a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-1-aug-25-worldwide-10-trump-s-south-asian-shift?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >Trump’s South Asian shift</a
            >).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
            <strong>🇱🇹 Lithuania - PM resigns.</strong> Lithuanian PM Gintautas
            Paluckas resigned amid a crime investigation and left his position
            as the head of the Social Democratic party. The probe involves the
            firms linked to him that used EU funds to trade battery systems from
            Garnis, a company partly owned by Paluckas. His departure follows
            coalition pressure, as they need to find a replacement within 60
            days (<a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-1-aug-25-worldwide-11-pressure-on-parliament?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >pressure on parliament</a
            >).
          </p>
